description: Prefer GitHub CLI (gh) for GitHub hosting operations; git for local commits
alwaysApply: true
---

# GitHub CLI first

Use **`gh`** for anything that talks to **GitHub.com** when it is available:

- Repos: `gh repo view`, `gh repo create`, `gh repo sync`, `gh browse`
- PRs: `gh pr create`, `gh pr list`, `gh pr checkout`, `gh pr merge`
- Issues / releases / workflows as needed: `gh issue`, `gh release`, `gh workflow`

Use **`git`** for local history: `git add`, `git commit`, `git status`, `git diff`, `git push`, `git pull`.

After `gh auth login`, **`gh auth setup-git`** should be configured so HTTPS Git operations reuse the same GitHub credentials without repeated browser prompts.

**Cursor agent:** Global auto-run for `gh` and `git` is configured in the user **`permissions.json`** (`terminalAllowlist`). **Agent → Auto-run** must still be set to **Run Everything** (or sandbox auto-run) in Cursor Settings; in **Ask Every Time** mode, allowlists are not applied.

Do not paste or commit tokens. Prefer `gh auth status` over echoing credentials.
